<h1 class="title">Blindspots</h1>
<p>
(by Marty Makary )
</p>

<p>
There should be some sense of uncertainty associated with all medical recommendations.
How sure are we that this is correct ? (eg: Bronze, Sliver, Gold) 
</p>

<p>
Every US medical school is controlled by a private company that has a monopoly on accredititng medical schools and writing examinations. 
</p>

<p>
Nature states openely that its policy is to remove articles that "might contradict widely accepted pubilc-health advice."
</p>

<p>
Woemen where not allowed to do their own pregnecy tests until 1976.
